<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-226-188 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 381 865</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Feb 4, 1991 v6 n132 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>International: Ericsson wins $90 million order to expand Turkey'stelecommunications network. (Ericsson Telekomunikasyon A.S.,andO;Turkish Telecommunications Administration)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ericsson Telekomunikasyon A.S. (Contracts).andO;Topic:     Government ContractsTelephone SystemsExpansionTurkeyTurkey. Telecommunications AdministrationEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Ericsson has received an additional order, valued at $90 million, from theTurkish Telecommunications Adminstration (PTT).andM;The order covers the expansion of Istanbul's local telecommunicationsnetwork.andP;  The contract has been placed with Ericsson's Turkish company,Ericsson Telekomunikasyon A.S.andM;&quot;The contract period runs from 1991 until 1993 and will involve theinstallation of approximately 300,000 lines this year,&quot; said Johan Bruce,Ericsson's manager in Turkey.andP;  &quot;With this contract, we have consolidated ourposition in the Turkish market, where we have been active in networkconstruction since 1986.andP;  Turkey is now one of Ericsson's most importantmarkets in this field.&quot;andM;The project will be started immediately.andP;  The network construction work willbe partly executed with the help of Turkish subcontractors.andM;This contract and the recently announced agreement to install cable TVnetworks in Turkey mean that Ericsson Telekomunikasyon has received ordersfrom the Turkish PTT valued at $144 million since the beginning of 1991.andM;Ericsson is an international leader in telecommunications, recognized for itsadvanced systems and products for wired and mobile communications in publicand private networks.andO;</TEXT></DOC>